schedule_summary: I prioritized staff fairness and peak-period coverage, resulting in a balanced 0.24 Gini score while filling over 92% of our total labor needs. To maintain this equity, I had to decline some individual shift preferences, particularly where availability was thin during weekend rushes. You currently have five remaining coverage gaps that I couldn't fill with the existing part-time roster, so I recommend hiring two additional seasonal servers or asking the core team for overtime volunteers to reach 100% capacity.
